	)
	(text "Manually set ROSC; by default, fsw = 120 kHz\nWith 200k resistor, fsw ≈ 525 kHz (Inverse)\n\nCss (nF) = (tss (ms) * Iss (uA) / Vref (V)\nIss = 2uA, Vref = 0.8V from datasheet\n\nTarget start time of 5ms\nCss = 5 * 2.5 = 12.5 nf ≈ 10 nF (std value)\n\nSchottky Catch Diode\nMust be > Vin; V > 8.4V, Handle 2A output current\n\nInductor \n\nL = ((Vout)*(Vin - Vout)) / ((Vin)(fsw)(ΔIl)\n- Target ΔIl = 0.3A\n\nL = ((5V)*(8.4-5)) / ((8.4)(525000)(0.3))\nL ≈ 12.8 uH\n10uH chosen for availability\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 236.982 92.71 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(color 0 0 0 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "79aee6f6-9b68-4701-bfdf-106c7f1eaa9e")
	)
	(text "π-Filter Ferrite Bead\n\nIsat = 1.5 * Inet\nIsat = 1.5 * 5 A ≈ 10 A\n\nLow heat dissipation. \nDCR = 10 mohm\n\nP = I^2 * DCR = (5A)^2 * (0.01) = 0.25 W (heat)"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 166.624 84.582 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(color 0 0 0 1)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "8a95bc39-591b-4837-8321-af61ec36841e")
	)
